name: equiformer-diffusion
one_line_profile: Equiformer-based diffusion model for protein design
detailed_description: Implementation of a denoising diffusion model for protein design utilizing Equiformer (SE(3)/E(3) equivariant attention) architecture for improved geometric modeling.

name: progen-jax
one_line_profile: Jax implementation of ProGen for protein language modeling
detailed_description: An implementation and replication of ProGen (Language Modeling for Protein Generation) using Jax, enabling protein sequence generation and analysis.

name: esmdiff
one_line_profile: Structure Language Models for Protein Conformation Generation
detailed_description: Codebase for 'Structure Language Models for Protein Conformation Generation', providing tools for generating protein conformations using language model techniques.

name: 3D-Generative-SBDD
one_line_profile: 3D Generative Model for Structure-Based Drug Design
detailed_description: A 3D generative model designed for Structure-Based Drug Design (SBDD), capable of generating ligand structures within protein binding pockets.

name: diffab
one_line_profile: Diffusion-based generative model for antibody design
detailed_description: A diffusion-based generative model for antigen-specific antibody design and optimization, focusing on the generation of antibody structures and sequences.

name: AlignInversePro
one_line_profile: Inference-Time Alignment in Protein Diffusion Models
detailed_description: A tool for inference-time alignment in protein diffusion models, allowing for better control and adherence to constraints during protein structure generation.

name: ProDifEvo-Refinement
one_line_profile: Evolutionary Algorithm with Diffusion Models for Protein Design
detailed_description: Combines evolutionary algorithms with diffusion models to refine and optimize protein designs.

name: SVDD
one_line_profile: Derivative-Free Guidance in Diffusion Models for Bio-sequences
detailed_description: Implements Soft Value-Based Decoding (SVDD) for derivative-free guidance in diffusion models, applicable to controlled generation of DNA, RNA, and proteins.

name: GelGenie
one_line_profile: Analysis of gel electrophoresis images using machine learning
detailed_description: An open-source package for the segmentation and analysis of gel electrophoresis images, providing both a Python framework and a QuPath GUI extension.

name: TopoDiff
one_line_profile: Global-geometry-aware diffusion for protein backbone generation
detailed_description: A diffusion-based model for protein backbone generation that incorporates global geometry-aware latent encoding to improve structure quality.

name: EvoDiff
one_line_profile: Discrete diffusion models for protein sequence generation
detailed_description: A framework for generating protein sequences and evolutionary alignments using discrete diffusion models, enabling the exploration of protein sequence space.

name: FoldingDiff
one_line_profile: Diffusion models for protein structure generation
detailed_description: A diffusion model based approach for generating protein backbone structures, utilizing angles and attention mechanisms.

name: Protein Frame Flow
one_line_profile: Fast protein backbone generation with SE(3) flow matching
detailed_description: A method for fast and efficient generation of protein backbones using SE(3) flow matching techniques.

name: salad
one_line_profile: Protein structure generation with sparse all-atom denoising
detailed_description: A model for generating protein structures using sparse all-atom denoising techniques, facilitating high-resolution structure synthesis.

name: nf-core/proteinfamilies
one_line_profile: Workflow for generation and updating of protein families
detailed_description: A Nextflow pipeline for the generation and updating of protein families, facilitating large-scale comparative genomics and protein classification.

name: NOS
one_line_profile: Protein Design with Guided Discrete Diffusion
detailed_description: A tool for protein design utilizing guided discrete diffusion models to generate sequences with desired properties.

name: EquiDock
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning for fast rigid 3D protein-protein docking
detailed_description: A geometric deep learning model for fast and accurate rigid 3D protein-protein docking, predicting the complex structure from unbound protein structures.

name: Path-Planning (P2)
one_line_profile: Masked diffusion model sampling method for sequence generation
detailed_description: A Python package implementing P2 (Path Planning), a sampling method for masked diffusion models applied to sequence generation tasks, including protein sequence generation.

name: protein-sequence-diffusion-model
one_line_profile: Diffusion model specifically designed for protein sequence generation
detailed_description: A diffusion-based generative model implementation focused on generating protein sequences, serving as a tool for exploring sequence space in protein engineering.

name: DiffDock-Pocket
one_line_profile: Diffusion-based pocket-level molecular docking tool
detailed_description: An implementation of DiffDock-Pocket that applies diffusion models to pocket-level docking with side chain flexibility, facilitating structure-based drug design.

name: RamaNet
one_line_profile: De novo protein design using machine learning
detailed_description: A tool for de novo protein design that leverages machine learning and PyRosetta to generate novel protein structures, focusing on Ramachandran plot constraints.

name: GGNN_Meets_PLM
one_line_profile: Integration of protein language models with geometric deep learning
detailed_description: A framework integrating pre-trained protein language models into geometric deep learning networks to enhance protein representation learning and structure-property prediction.

name: DiffDock (Colab)
one_line_profile: Colab implementation of DiffDock for molecular docking
detailed_description: A ready-to-use Colab notebook implementation of DiffDock, facilitating the application of diffusion models for molecular docking tasks without local setup.

name: MolScribe
one_line_profile: Image-to-graph generation for molecular structure recognition
detailed_description: A robust tool for recognizing molecular structures from images and converting them into graph representations, useful for digitizing chemical literature and data extraction.

name: DeepPBS
one_line_profile: Geometric deep learning for protein-DNA binding specificity
detailed_description: A geometric deep learning tool designed to predict protein-DNA binding specificity, aiding in the understanding of regulatory mechanisms and structural biology.

name: GENIE3
one_line_profile: Inference of gene regulatory networks from expression data
detailed_description: A classic machine learning-based tool for inferring gene regulatory networks from gene expression data, widely used in systems biology.

name: Evolla (ProteinChat)
one_line_profile: Protein-language generative model for decoding molecular language
detailed_description: A frontier protein-language generative model (ProteinChat) designed to decode and generate the molecular language of proteins, facilitating protein design and analysis.

name: FLAG
one_line_profile: Molecule Generation for Target Protein Binding with Structural Motifs
detailed_description: A 3D generative model for structure-based drug design that generates molecules binding to specific protein targets while incorporating structural motifs. Implementation of the ICLR 2023 paper.

name: PocketFlow
one_line_profile: Generalized Protein Pocket Generation with Prior-Informed Flow Matching
detailed_description: A generative model for creating protein pockets using prior-informed flow matching, facilitating the design of novel binding sites. Implementation of the NeurIPS 2024 paper.

name: GeoBind
one_line_profile: Segmentation of nucleic acid binding interface on protein surface
detailed_description: A geometric deep learning tool for segmenting and predicting nucleic acid binding interfaces on protein surfaces, aiding in the analysis of protein-DNA/RNA interactions.
